Antonio Miguel Ferreira Marques Trindade wrote:
> 
>    There is a patch running around that permits you to have VESAfb on S3
> cards with a 1.2 VBE BIOS. My question is: Is it going to be part of the
> mainstream kernels or not?
doubtful, it is a pretty big (though useful) hack
A framebuffer driver for Trios exists at
http://www.hut.fi/~hmallat/linux/s3.html
I hope to merge in PPC support and maybe Amiga support too from existing
S3triofb and cyberfb drivers, so there is finally one unified driver.
